div.h1: Context Switch Assembly: ESP Pivot Sequence
div.p: context_switch_asm(old_esp_ptr, new_esp, new_cr3) called with IF=0 from sched_schedule()

ul.li: Purple: Next process saved frame / iret fields

div.p: The pivot is NOT atomic in the OS sense but IF=0 guarantees no interrupt fires between steps and .

text.tspan: ; ESP now points into NEXT process stack
mov cr3, edx ; flush non-global TLB
; pops return addr from NEXT process stack
ret pops this jumps to trampoline
trampoline: pop eax; mov gs, ax
trampoline: pop eax; mov ds, ax (last)
and switches back to user stack

g.text: pop eax; mov gs, ax ; restore GS
pop eax; mov fs, ax ; restore FS
pop eax; mov es, ax ; restore ES
pop eax; mov ds, ax ; restore DS

text.tspan: CPU reads esp0 on next ring-3 interrupt
uses correct kernel stack for new process
